  "culturalTip": "Prior to the Seoul Olympics in 1988, the Korean government placed many restrictions on traveling abroad, until 1989 when the restrictions were lifted and people were allowed to travel freely. Now, only Korean men over 24 who have not completed their compulsory military service have some restrictions (they have to get additional permission from the Military Manpower Administration). Many low-cost Korean airlines began operating in the late 2000s, leading to a steady increase in the number of people from Korea traveling abroad.",
